The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, gave a speech at the Hidden Heroes 3rd Annual National Convening in Washington, D.C. He expressed gratitude to the military and veteran caregivers who support wounded veterans, calling them America's Hidden Heroes. Pence discussed the challenges that caregivers face and acknowledged the sacrifices they make. He also highlighted the efforts of the Elizabeth Dole Foundation in supporting caregivers and announced the naming of the VA's new Center of Excellence for Veteran and Caregiver Research after Senator Elizabeth Dole. Pence pledged the administration's commitment to supporting veterans and their caregivers, mentioning initiatives such as the VA Mission Act and Veterans Choice. He emphasized the importance of honoring and supporting those who serve in the military and their families. Pence concluded by urging everyone to do more to support and uplift these heroes and their caregivers.